title: ASUS ZenFone 3 Go render and specs leaked, all-metal design and selfie flash in tow
text:
ASUS ZenFone 3 Go render and specs leaked, all-metal design and selfie... ASUS ZenFone 3 Go render and specs leaked, all-metal design and selfie flash in tow By February 17, 2017 “The ZenFone 3 Go will bring a premium metal-unibody design and a selfie flash” 
It appears that ASUS is all set to add a budget smartphone to the ZenFone 3 range, Dubbed the ASUS ZenFone 3 Go, the upcoming phone’s alleged render and specifications have been tipped. Unlike the previous ZenFone Go series phones, the ZenFone 3 Go will share most of its aesthetics with the rest of the ZenFone 3 family including a premium metal unibody design. 
As seen in the renders, the metal-clad ASUS ZenFone 3 Go will be available in a range of hues. The phone will have capacitive buttons for navigation. The source suggests that the device will come with a 5-inch HD display, and will be powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 410 SoC. It will offer 2GB of RAM and 16GB of internal storage, which will probably be further expandable. 
The ASUS ZenFone 3 Go will sport a 13-megapixel primary shooter and a 5-megapixel secondary shooter. The render also suggests that the phone will get a soft LED flash for brighter selfies, dual MEMS mics and a five-magnet speaker with a smart amp. It will be priced at around Rs 10,700, adds the source. The brand is expected to officially unveil the device in the coming weeks.
